===

title: Opening
---
A moment that happened fifteen years ago feels like it was yesterday.
Lashes fluttered towards the neck of her gifted spruce violin. Her fingers danced across strings with methodic passion.
She played notes of Heaven from her shoulder, enchanting the nation as much as a young prodigy could.
My hands shook across piano keys while I struggled to keep up. I was confused. I didn't know yet what I wanted from life.
All I knew in that instance was that I wanted <i>her</i>.
<<jump Dialogue1>>
===

title:Dialogue1
---
<<setVex vexTired>>
VEX: Recording: Day 71 of attempting to nurse the most important project I’ve ever had back to health. 
VEX: EL1-5e.
VEX: 71 long days of tweaking, researching, venturing outdoors to scavenge for parts, and coming back to try all over again.
VEX: It’s grueling work, being by my lonesome while I try and make a miracle happen.
VEX: All I need is to do is power the unit on to make sure its body works. It doesn’t even need to talk back to me, yet. 
VEX: God, I miss talking to people. I wish I could have a conversation with someone. With anyone.
VEX: I keep telling myself to keep it together. That I will succeed and it’s only a matter of time before I can get its systems up and running.
VEX: And only after I get its systems on can I hope to speak with her again.
VEX: T-3. Unit T-3. Why have I never seen this model before? Why can I hardly find any information about it online?
VEX: Sigh. I suppose there are still routing combinations with its internal circuitry I haven’t tried, yet.
<<runMaintenance 1>>
<<endDialogue end>>
===

title:Dialogue2
---
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Okay. It’s a long shot, but–
<<setVex vexSurprised>>
VEX: . . . !
<<setRobo roboWhiteEyes>>
EL1-5e: Hello. Welcome ASCO UNIT T-3, a companion to suit all your flying needs.
EL1-5e: My name has been set to EL1-5e. Please prepare for me to awaken momentarily.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
Oh shit. Oh God, it’s on. Why’s it sound like that? Let me consult my manual, and –
<<setRobo roboSurprised>>
EL1-5e: H-h-hello? 
<<setVex vexSurprised>>
VEX:AH!
<<setRobo roboSurprised>>
EL1-5e:Ah?
<<setVex vexSurprised>>
VEX: Why do you sound like that?
VEX: Do you know who you are?
<<setRobo roboSurprised>>
EL1-5e: I-I am EL1-5e–
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: No, no! I mean. . . do you know who I am?
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: I. . . I do not believe I have seen you before, no.
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX:She’s not supposed to sound like that. Did I do something wrong?
<<setRobo roboConfused>>
EL1-5e: Excuse me. Where am I?
<<hideSprites sprites>>
<<playSound 2>>
I scramble through the files on my computer in a flurry of clicks. This is definitely further than I’ve gotten, but not exactly what I was aiming for.
<<setRobo roboConfused>>
EL1-5e: Who are you?
<<setVex VexGlasses>>
VEX: Why is it speaking to me right now? And how?
<<setRobo roboConfused>>
EL1-5e: . . . Am I even alive?
<<setVex VexGlasses>>
VEX: I can’t work with all this noise. Need to figure out how to power it off–
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: PLEASE!
<<hideSprites sprites>>
I halt in my tracks.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: Please don’t. I am afraid that if you power me down, I may never wake up again.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
The thing’s so much more animated than it has been the last 71 days. Moving its head from side to side, widening its eyes, chest and shoulders tensing. Looking like it’s trying to break free from its constraints and failing. As if it has power pumping through its systems, but not enough to operate at full capacity.
Signs of primal fear. Like a rabbit cornered.
Whatever I did, it looks like it may have worked, in a roundabout way.
<<jump Dialogue3>>
===

title: Dialogue3
---
<<showCG 2>>
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Oh my gosh. I wasn’t expecting this. How fascinating.
<<setRobo roboConfused>>
EL1-5e: A-am. . . am I not to your satisfaction?
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: Hmm. That depends on whether you can help me out or not.
<<setRobo roboBlush>>
EL1-5e: W-why, yes. Allow me to answer your questions.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: I sound this way because that is how I was manufactured by Artificial Sentience Corporation Omega.
EL1-5e: I am ASCO UNIT T-3, designed as a companion to service passengers on flights all over the world, otherwise dubbed EL1-5e in my project files.
EL1-5e: I do not know who you are.
EL1-5e: I am speaking to you because I am confused.
EL1-5e: And afraid.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
Oh. Not only can it speak and emote, it can also understand me and retain a shocking amount of memory. This is a massive upgrade from the last I’d seen of ASCO’s robotics department.
I haven't been able to ride a plane for the last ten years. So, no wonder I’ve never seen one of these units before.
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX: Okay. Thanks for answering my earlier questions. Let me see if I can help you out in return.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: This is my lab.
VEX: My name is VEX. I am the engineer that repaired you back to the state you are in now.
VEX: And, while ‘alive’ can be difficult to define, the fact that you are capable of showing fear is a good sign. So, for simplicity’s sake, let’s say. . . yes, you are alive, indeed.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
EL1-5e looks contemplatively around at her surroundings, down at the state of her weathered body, and finally, back to me.
<<setRobo roboConfused>>
EL1-5e: What happened? I would assume I am under maintenance, but I am not usually in a. . .
EL1-5e: . . . place like this.
<<setVex vexTired>>
VEX: Okay, I get it. My lab isn’t exactly the 5-star ASCO maintenance shops you’re probably used to. But this is my home, and this is what I’ve got to work with.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Feel free to leave a rating on YELL. Hehe.
<<setRobo roboConfused>>
EL1-5e: Ah. . .
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: That was a joke. Not a good one. That’s okay.
<<setRobo roboBlush>>
EL1-5e: I’m sorry. I didn’t mean to offend you.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Never apologize.
VEX: Listen to me. I’ll tell you only once what happened to you, EL1, but then I’ve got to get back to work. You are just such a scientific marvel to me, I’ve got to poke around you some more. Understand?
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: . . . I do.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: 71 days ago, I found you in an ASCO scrapyard.
VEX: There were a lot of your kind there. Some whole, some not, and almost all of them unusable.
VEX: But the moment I saw you, I knew you had to be the one.
VEX: I’ve been fixing you up since, all by my lonesome. 71 days is a long time to be working on something with no success, as you might know, so I was very close to giving up.
VEX: I’m so glad that you’ve woken up now.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: . . . So that means you’ve saved me.
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX: Hmm. In a way, yes!
VEX: But you’re still a long way from being good-as-new. So if you don’t mind, I’m going to power you down so I can keep working on you, now.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: NO!
<<hideSprites sprites>>
Her shrill yell echoes against the laboratory once more. Her limbs tense and whir, fighting against her constraints.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: Please don’t. I’m scared that I’m not going to wake up. Please keep me on.
EL1-5e: I will behave. I always have. I promise.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
...Now that I think about it, I suppose it is possible to perform maintenance while the AI is still powered on. In fact, engineers may benefit from it so they can receive live feedback.
Kind of like orthodontists knowing when to pull back if the kid starts screaming.
With the state that EL1-5e is in, I can’t afford to not be careful.
Besides, there’s something about the way it looks that makes me feel kind of. . .
. . . bad for it, in a way?
<<setVex vexTired>>
VEX: Alright. I’ll keep you on for now. But listen, I’m kind of a washed-up engineer, so I don’t. . . fully know what I’m doing.
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: Just, you know. Scream if it hurts.
<<startDay 1>>
<<endDialogue end>>
===
