title: Dialogue4
---
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: If I may ask. . . why have you brought me here?
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX:All that’s left is to log my progress for the day. So much to write down. I’ll need to make sure my backup servers are still in order. Not to mention. . .
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: I sense you are busy. . .
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX: Ah, and I’ll need to power you off for the night. I’m the sole owner of this laboratory, so, you know. . . that also means I’m paying for the electricity here on my own.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: I-I’m sorry. . .
EL1-5e: I don’t feel comfortable powering off, just yet.
<<setVex vexConfused>>
VEX: You can trust me. Besides, won’t you get bored? You’ll be here alone in the dark for the next ten hours or so.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: I enjoy meditative periods of alone time. 
EL1-5e: My service role was that of a flight attendant. On long flights, we would be stored in compartments by the cockpit, but kept awake in case of emergency.
EL1-5e: That was where I learned to enjoy solitude. I will not be bored. I will appreciate the time awake.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: Please, I beg you.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
So she won’t be bored if I leave her alone, but I’ve barely got the funds to keep myself afloat.
EL1-5e, at least in the form she’s in now, is meant to be a short-term companion. So, does it really matter whether I tend to her every concern or not?
-> Keep her powered on
   <<jump choice1a>>
-> Power her off
   <<jump choice1b>>
<<jump flashback1>>
===

title: choice1a
---
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Fine, you’ve convinced me.
VEX: Lights will be off. I’ll be gone for the next ten hours. And I’ll still need to lower your power capacitor for the night. But, you will remain powered on.
<<setRobo roboHappy>>
EL1-5e: Ah. . . I will stay perfectly quiet and still the entire night.
EL1-5e: Thank you so much, VEX.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: No problem, EL1-5e.
<<setVex vexConfused>>
VEX: That’s a little bit of a mouthful now that I’m speaking in a conversation with you. How about I just call you EL1?
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: That is a perfectly suitable name for me. Whatever you wish, VEX.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
Of course she’s going to agree with it. Really no point in my asking for her permission.
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: Right. Well, see you tomorrow, EL1.
<<jump flashback1>>
===

title: choice1b
---
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: Rest assured, as a seasoned engineer, you’ll be just fine. You won’t even realize you were asleep. One moment you’re here, and the next moment, it’s the morning.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: Wait, wait, wait –
<<playSound 3>>
<<setRobo roboClosedEyes>>
There we go. I’ve just saved myself a couple hundred dollars in bills.
Even though I do feel a little bad for her. It doesn’t matter too much in the long run.
<<endDialogue end>>
<<jump flashback1>>
===

